instructor.bio: Growing up in a household of athletes in Chicago and majoring in kinesiology in college, Chase knew that fitness and movement would play a big role in his life. It was while working in physical therapy at a sports medicine clinic that Chase fell in love with helping people improve their lives through fitness. Chase has also worked as a personal trainer, bootcamp instructor and lifestyle coach, and brings his positive outlook and passion for helping people improve their confidence to his Peloton Tread classes.
instructor.short_bio: "It’s what you do in the dark that puts you in the light."
instructor.background: I want Members to approach my workouts by looking at the big picture. Our time together will be so much deeper than just “working out” or “being fit.” It will be about showing up to conquer what’s in front of us.
ordered_q_and_as: I want Members to approach my workouts as so much more than just that. This is so much deeper than just “working out” or “being fit.”
I’m always learning. This can come in many of forms: cooking, traveling, reading, dancing, coaching, acting and more.
instructor.quote: It’s what you do in the dark that puts you in the light.
instructor.name: Chase Tucker
